(43, 4, 13, 42, 16, 24, 24, 'thirst again', 'Theme of Thirst and Water', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of thirst, with John 4:13 stating that those who drink from the well will thirst again, while Luke 16:24 depicts a plea for water to cool a tormented tongue. This connection highlights the spiritual and physical implications of thirst.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
